Tanzania is set to get USD 75m that will be used to improve vocational skills in the country. The fund comes through the East Africa Skills for Transformation and Regional Integration Project (EASTRIP) that will be launched in Ethiopia, next month. The project that covers Tanzania, Kenya and Ethiopia is funded by the World Bank and its main objective is to boost the number of technical vocational education and training (TVET) programs in the selected countries. Launching the first phase of the project which will be facilitated by the Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation (SDC), the Minister of Education, Science and Technology Professor Joyce Ndalichako said in Dar es Salaam early of Friday that: “This is part of the government’s plan to empower Tanzanians especially youths with vocational skills so as to have enough skilled labour.”   